The women of Ijaw extraction, under the platform of Kalabari-Ijaw mothers and daughters, have urged the  Federal Government to carry out a thorough investigation into the circumstances that led to the killings at Abonnema in Akuku-Torlu Local Government Area of Rivers State during the Saturday’s elections. Over 10 persons reportedly lost their lives in Abonnema when soldiers engaged some youths of the community in a shootout. Addressing newsmen in Port Harcourt yesterday, their leader, Ms Annkio Briggs, said the killings  in Abonnema and other places in Rivers State must be investigated and criminal proceedings commenced immediately against all those found culpable. Rivers traditional ruler in ‘witchcraft’ tango 2 children drown in Rivers Heavy gunfire, sporadic shooting in Abonnema , Bonny